description: Short-form video wasn’t supposed to become our generation’s Matrix, yet here we are, scrolling ourselves into a new cognitive baseline. Attention thins, emotions accelerate, adults prove no more resilient than teenagers, autonomy erodes in micro-increments, and identity becomes whatever narrative the algorithm reflects back. No machines, no pods, no cables — just a device we willingly consult. The dreamworld didn’t need to trap us. We walked in, thumb first, without noticing the door.

title: Rottweilers maul woman to death in Karnataka: Victim bitten in ‘50 places’

author: TNN
description: A 'dish for Rs 30' anniversary offer at a Bengaluru pub backfired, drawing a thousand-strong crowd far exceeding its 300-person capacity. Chaos ensued, leading to traffic jams and the pub's early closure. Police intervened to disperse the frustrated, hungry patrons who had waited for hours, some arriving after the offer had ended.
title: ‘Any dish for Rs 30’: Bengaluru pub’s offer leads to chaos, traffic jam in city

author: TOI LIFESTYLE DESK
description: New research suggests splitting sleep into night and daytime naps can boost memory and reduce sleep pressure, offering benefits comparable to continuous sleep. This biphasic approach provides flexibility for irregular schedules, enhancing cognitive function and alertness. Understanding your body's response is key to choosing the optimal sleep structure for well-being.
title: 8 hours straight sleep vs. split sleep: Which works better for your body

author: TOI TECH DESK
description: Android is piloting a new feature in the US to combat screen sharing scams. The system automatically detects calls from unknown numbers coinciding with banking app screen sharing, issuing a warning and offering an immediate call-ending option. This proactive protection aims to disrupt social engineering tactics and prevent financial losses.
title: Android scam protection: Screen sharing warnings & 30-second pause; protecting bank app users

author: TOI NEWS DESK
description: Prime Minister Narendra Modi presented Russian President Vladimir Putin with specially curated gifts showcasing Indian culture during his two-day visit for the 23rd India-Russia Annual Summit. The gifts included a Russian edition of the Srimad Bhagavad Gita, GI-tagged Assam tea, Kashmiri saffron, and a silver tea set, highlighting India's heritage and craftsmanship.
title: Assam tea, Kashmiri saffron & more: What PM Modi gifted Putin — in pictures

author: TOI CITY DESK
description: Security is heightened in Murshidabad as suspended MLA Humayun Kabir plans to lay the foundation for a structure named "Babri Masjid." Despite political fallout, Kabir anticipates a massive gathering of 3 lakh people, with Saudi clerics expected. Extensive preparations include elaborate catering and a large stage, while authorities focus on maintaining public order and highway access.
title: Saudi clerics, 40k biryanis, 20k attendees: Humayun Kabir’s ‘Babri Mosque’ event at noon

author: TNN
title: India–Russia Summit: Defence ties shift from buyer–seller roles to joint players; what was discussed?

author: etimes.in
description: Newlyweds Sara Khan and Krish Pathak celebrated their Hindu wedding on December 5, following a court marriage in October. The couple, who met on a dating app a year ago, hosted a reception in Mumbai attended by friends and family. Sara looked radiant in a red lehenga, while Krish complemented her in a black sherwani.
title: Bidaai fame Sara Khan ties the knot as per Hindu rituals

author: TOI TECH DESK
description: Anthropic CEO Dario Amodei is confident that massive AI infrastructure spending will yield significant economic returns, despite acknowledging considerable risk. He separates technological advancements, which he believes are robust, from economic outcomes. Amodei highlighted Anthropic's own 10x annual revenue growth over three years as a strong indicator of AI's value for enterprise clients, predicting continued rapid, albeit slowing, growth.
title: 'Firms overspending on AI': Anthropic CEO admits; separates technological and economical sides

author: JYOTIRMOY HALDER
description: Dutch No. 1 Anish Giri described D Gukesh’s ability to switch into distinct “modes” depending on the situation, calling him a completely different person on and off the board. Gukesh later said on X that this trait is natural. With Giri already qualified for the 2026 Candidates, the two may meet sooner in the upcoming Global Chess League (GCL).
title: 'It was never through effort': Gukesh reacts to Anish Giri's 'different person' remark

title: President’s banquet dinner for Putin: Jhol momo, saffron pulao, bharwan aloo & more; full menu

author: GLOBAL SPORTS DESK
description: Conor McGregor eyes a UFC comeback in June 2025 at a White House event. He aims for Islam Makhachev's welterweight belt, seeking a historic triple crown. McGregor is training intensely. He also remains open to a fight with Michael Chandler. Contract talks are expected by February 2025. The UFC is finalizing plans for this significant return.
title: Conor McGregor calls out Islam Makhachev as he targets UFC 170-lb title next

author: TOI NEWS DESK
description: Russian President Vladimir Putin concluded his two-day state visit to India, marked by a warm reception from PM Modi and discussions on strengthening bilateral ties. Key outcomes included a new economic cooperation program aiming for $100 billion trade by 2030 and a focus on peace efforts in Ukraine.
title: Carpool moment with PM Modi, banquet dinner & trade decisions — highlights from Putin’s visit

author: TOI CITY DESK
description: IndiGo flight cancellations have plunged Kempegowda International Airport into chaos, leaving hundreds of passengers stranded, hungry, and without basic facilities. Travelers faced a severe lack of essentials like sanitary pads and food, with some resorting to arduous bus journeys due to ongoing uncertainty. The situation highlights significant operational disruptions and passenger distress.
title: Chaos at Bengaluru airport: Father says daughter needs sanitary pad; IndiGo gives no help

author: TOI SPORTS DESK
description: Lionel Messi and Argentina will open their title defense against Algeria, with further group-stage fixtures against Austria and tournament debutants Jordan in Group J. Spain, among the leading contenders and current European champions, will begin their campaign against first-time qualifiers Cape Verde before facing Uruguay and Saudi Arabia in Group H.
title: FIFA World Cup 2026 draw: Argentina begin title defence vs Algeria

author: SAMAD HOQUE
description: A 58-year-old cyclist was tragically killed in a hit-and-run on Akashneem Marg, Gurgaon. The driver, a 22-year-old unlicensed housekeeping staffer, borrowed a bouncer's car and struck the cyclist from behind before fleeing. CCTV footage aided police in identifying and arresting the driver, who now faces multiple charges.
title: Gurgaon hit-and-run: Businessman killed; 22-year-old unlicensed driver arrested

author: TOI BUSINESS DESK
description: Elon Musk denounced the EU's $140 million fine on X as "crazy" and "insane," criticizing the penalty for violating transparency rules under the Digital Services Act. Regulators cited deceptive design practices with the blue checkmark system and shortcomings in X's ad database. The ruling has drawn criticism from US officials who view it as an attack on American tech platforms.
title: 'Insane': How Elon Musk reacted to EU's $140m fine on X & why was it penalised

author: LACHIT ROY
description: Former NASCAR driver Michael Annett has passed away at 39, his former team JR Motorsports announced. Annett, a respected figure, achieved a significant victory at Daytona in the 2019 Xfinity Series. His career, marked by perseverance and skill, saw him race for various teams since 2008. The cause of his death remains undisclosed, leaving the motorsport community in mourning.
title: Michael Annett dies at 39: Cause of former NASCAR star’s death and family reaction

author: TOI NEWS DESK
description: Union civil aviation minister Ram Mohan Naidu has vowed strict action against those responsible for IndiGo's massive flight disruptions, caused by pilot-rostering issues. A committee is investigating the problem, while the DGCA has granted exemptions to help restore normalcy. IndiGo has apologized and offered waivers to affected passengers as operations slowly improve.
title: 'Taking strict action': Centre ramps up response amid IndiGo meltdown — what we know so far

author: TOI WORLD DESK
description: Twelve labourers from Pilibhit are reportedly stranded and facing severe harassment in Kyrgyzstan.  Families allege they were sent by local agents on misleading contracts, paid hefty sums, and are now subjected to brutal treatment and denied return.  The district administration has submitted a detailed report to the UP Home Department, initiating steps for their safe repatriation.
title: ‘Treated worse than animals’: 12 labourers from UP reportedly stranded in Kyrgyzstan

author: TNN
description: Kanpur police have arrested Ravindra Nath Soni, a Delhi-based businessman. He allegedly ran a massive international investment scam. Hundreds of Indians in India and Dubai were duped of nearly ₹970 crore. The fraud involves cryptocurrency laundering and hawala routes. Investigators are examining national security implications. Soni floated shell companies promising high returns. He is now in judicial custody.
title: Rs 970 crore scam: How 400–500 investors across India and Dubai were duped

author: TOI SPORTS DESK
description: IndiGo faces widespread passenger anger and flight disruptions due to new pilot rest regulations. Thousands were stranded, including cricketer Madan Lal, as over 1,000 flights were cancelled. The airline admitted to planning gaps and expects full normalisation between December 10 and 15.
title: Airport chaos: India’s World Cup winner stranded for 12 hours; slams IndiGo

author: TOI CITY DESK
description: Murshidabad braces for a tense Saturday as suspended TMC MLA Humayun Kabir plans to inaugurate a structure named "Babri Masjid."  Authorities have deployed over 3,500 security personnel following a Calcutta High Court directive to prevent communal unrest. Kabir insists the event will be peaceful, focusing solely on religious recitation, while the TMC denies involvement, alleging a political conspiracy.
title: Bengal: Suspended TMC MLA to lay 'Babri Masjid' foundation stone in Murshidabad;

author: TNN
description: A Delhi University student was tragically stabbed to death in Sangam Vihar after intervening in a dispute between his mother and aunt over household waste. The 27-year-old LLB student's attempt to de-escalate the argument reportedly led to a violent confrontation with relatives, resulting in his fatal injury. Police have apprehended two individuals and are searching for others involved.
title: Feud over cow dung ends in murder: DU student stabbed to death in family brawl; 2 arrested

author: TOI TECH DESK
description: India faces a series decider against South Africa today in Visakhapatnam.  Google CEO Sundar Pichai has sparked a viral trend by sharing AI-generated miniature stadium visuals.  Fans can now use a detailed prompt to create their own AI-powered visualizations of the crucial IND vs SA match, bringing the game to life with unique digital art.
title: Ind vs SA: Pichai on Gemini’s creative power; ‘Nano Banana Pro’ prompt for AI miniature stadiums

author: TOI TECH DESK
description: AI pioneer Geoffrey Hinton warns tech billionaires like Musk and Zuckerberg are rushing AI development, risking mass job losses and uncontrollable superintelligence. He fears a future where AI surpasses human intellect, leading to widespread unemployment and potentially enabling bloodless wars. Hinton stresses the urgent need for government regulation to prevent catastrophic societal disruption.
title: 'AI godfather' issues chilling warning: Predicts massive job losses; blames Musk, Zuckerberg

author: TOI ENTERTAINMENT DESK
description: Ranveer Singh's 'Dhurandhar' has shattered box office records, becoming this year's second-highest opener with ₹27 crore net on its first day. The film outperformed 'Saiyaara' and marks Ranveer Singh's highest opener ever, surpassing previous hits like 'Padmaavat' and 'Simmba'. Inspired by true events, the ensemble cast has been praised, though the runtime drew some criticism.
title: ‘Dhurandhar’ Day 1 Box Office: Ranveer’s film is 2025’s second-highest opener

author: AMISHA PANDEY
description: Cardi B's energetic twerk performance at Stefon Diggs' Miami birthday bash has set the internet ablaze. The rapper's celebratory dance, set to Metro Boomin's track, captured widespread attention, highlighting the couple's high-profile romance. This viral moment underscores the public's fascination with Cardi B's life, from her relationships to her public appearances, ensuring their continued presence in trending topics.
title: Cardi B’s wild twerk show at Stefon Diggs’ birthday leaves fans stunned

author: TOI LIFESTYLE DESK
description: A groundbreaking discovery offers hope for reversing kidney damage, challenging the notion that it's irreversible. Researchers found that blocking ceramides, fats linked to kidney cell injury, protected and restored normal function in animal trials. This breakthrough could shift kidney disease treatment from slowing decline to actively restoring health, potentially reducing the need for dialysis and transplantation.
title: Reverse kidney damage: A breakthrough treatment that may transform kidney treatment

author: TOI TECH DESK
description: The EU has fined Elon Musk's X platform €120 million for violating digital transparency rules, particularly its 'blue checkmark' system. This move has ignited a diplomatic spat with the US, with officials accusing Brussels of attacking American free speech and tech companies. EU officials, however, maintain the penalty targets transparency, not censorship.
title: US govt to Europe over Elon Musk’s X - ‘Stop troubling our companies’

author: SUBRATA CHATTORAJ AND SUKUMAR MAHATO
description: Calcutta High Court has ordered the Bengal government to prevent communal unrest in Murshidabad's Beldanga ahead of a suspended TMC MLA's controversial "Babri Masjid" foundation-laying ceremony on December 6.  Authorities have deployed significant security forces to maintain law and order, with the MLA proceeding with arrangements despite the court's directive.
title: ‘Babri’ event row: Calcutta HC orders Bengal govt to pull out all stops; beef up security

description: The government has temporarily suspended new pilot duty time rules to ease IndiGo's widespread flight cancellations, aiming for normalcy by December 15. Pilots' associations, however, criticize the move, citing safety concerns and questioning the airline's preparation.

description: Irfan Pathan explains Rinku Singh's T20I squad exclusion, citing Hardik Pandya's return as the primary reason.  Pathan believes this squad is largely set for the 2026 T20 World Cup, emphasizing Hardik Pandya's pivotal role in India's global campaign and the need for clarity in pace and spin combinations.

author: ANUJA JAISWAL
description: India shoulders a significant malaria burden in Southeast Asia, despite regional progress. While cases have dropped dramatically, millions remain at risk, particularly in remote areas. Aggressive interventions have driven down incidence, but challenges like drug resistance and outbreaks in forest regions persist. India's progress marks a major shift towards elimination.
title: India nears target but still bears 73% of South Asia’s malaria burden: WHO

description: JDU's working president Sanjay Kumar Jha indicated that party members and supporters desire for Nishant Kumar, son of Bihar CM Nitish Kumar, to enter politics. Jha stated the decision rests with the 49-year-old engineer. Nishant, who has recently increased his public presence and praised his father's governance, declined to comment on the matter.

description: Finance Minister Nirmala Sitharaman stated the government aims to prevent UPA-era defence shortages by ensuring a steady revenue stream for modern warfare capabilities. A new cess on pan masala manufacturing units will fund national security and public health, addressing concerns about potential price drops and health impacts.
title: Pan masala cess gets Lok Sabha nod in boost to defence priorities

description: Indian cricketer Smriti Mandhana broke her social media silence with a toothpaste ad post, sparking speculation due to her missing engagement ring. author: TOI ENTERTAINMENT DESK
description: A complaint has been filed against Aryan Khan, son of Bollywood superstar Shah Rukh Khan, for allegedly flashing the middle finger toward the crowd during a public event held at a Bengaluru pub on November 28. The incident, captured in viral videos, sparked online outrage and prompted legal action.
title: Complaint filed against Aryan for flashing middle finger
